         <abstract>
            <p>A man repairing the inside of a water storage tank was injured after he fell 25—30 ft to the bottom of the empty tank, where he was trapped for three hours. He wasn't wearing a safety harness, and he was working alone. It was only after he failed to clock out at the end of his shift that someone checked on him.</p>
